        "title": "Specify logger level in log4j2 via JMX for unregistered loggers",
        "body": "<p>I use JMX client to change logger level in log4j programatically. It works fine, but how can specify logger level for non-registered (that aren't specified in log4j2.xml) loggers?<\/p>\n\n<p>For instance I have the following loggers block:<\/p>\n\n<pre class=\"lang-xml prettyprint-override\"><code>&lt;Loggers&gt;\n        &lt;Root level=\"WARN\"&gt;\n            &lt;AppenderRef ref=\"async\"/&gt;\n        &lt;/Root&gt;\n        &lt;Logger name=\"com.example\" level=\"INFO\" /&gt;\n        &lt;Logger name=\"com.example.java\" level=\"INFO\" /&gt;\n&lt;/Loggers&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>I have \"com.example\" and \"com.example.java\" loggers available for using via JMX. But what if I need specify logger level for \"com.example.java.Runner\" or for \"com.example.groovy\"? <\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 28117142,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "log4j",
            "jmx",
            "log4j2",
            "mbeans"
        ],
        "score": 1,
        "is_answered": false,
        "view_count": 2207
